comments: Blue and black colored dots are easily mistaken when close to each other
I used the strategy of finding extremes and drawing a line connecting those trying to vary the slope according to the data distribution.
I'm not trying to be offensive but I think you may have a drop in quality of your responses in the later part of the survey if people get bored.

The clearance of the scatterplots depends on the color of the plots where the green and red weren't clear when spread all over the graph but the black and blue where clearly noticeable even if they are distributed all over the graph.
